# Villa Kroløkke - Coding Rules

## Language & Tone
- Always use "jeg" (I) form, never "vi" (we) form
- This is a private daycare run by one person (Lisa Kroløkke)
- Use Danish language throughout the website
- Keep tone warm, friendly, and professional

## Code Style
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Follow consistent indentation (spaces, not tabs)
- Use descriptive class names following BEM-like conventions
- Keep CSS organized with clear sections
- Use modern CSS features (CSS variables, flexbox, grid)
- Ensure responsive design for mobile, tablet, and desktop

## File Structure
- HTML files: Use descriptive names (e.g., `om-mig.html`, `praktisk-info.html`)
- CSS: Single `styles.css` file with organized sections
- JavaScript: Single `script.js` file for all functionality
- Images: Store in `assets/` folder

## Content Guidelines
- Always refer to Lisa Kroløkke in first person ("jeg")
- Use "privat pasningsordning" NOT "privat dagpleje"
- Mention her background: trained nurse (sygeplejerske) and mother of 4 children (ages 7 months to 12 years)
- Location: Rismarksvej 14, 5200 Odense V i Bolbro (always mention Bolbro when referring to location)
- Phone: 40 62 61 66
- Opening hours: 7:00-16:00 Monday-Friday
- Price: 9,200 kr/month, with municipality subsidy of 6,498 kr (2025)
- Payment: Fixed transfer to account on first weekday of month

## Design
- Use light earth tones (beige, cream, light brown, terracotta)
- Modern, clean design
- Ensure good readability and accessibility
- Use appropriate spacing and typography

## Navigation
- Use dropdown menus for grouped content
- Keep navigation consistent across all pages
- Mark active page in navigation

## Testing
- Test on multiple screen sizes
- Ensure all links work correctly
- Verify images load properly
- Check Danish language accuracy

